---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="confiture - PostgreSQL Migrations | FraiseQL"
  description="Fast, deterministic database migrations. 600× faster than traditional migration tools. Supports DDL builds, incremental, production sync, and multi-agent strategies."
>
  <div style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1>🍓 confiture</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #666;">
      <strong>PostgreSQL Migrations</strong> – Fast, deterministic schema changes
    </p>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>What It Does</h2>
      <p>
        confiture is a migration orchestrator that optimizes PostgreSQL schema
        changes for speed and consistency.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>600× faster builds</strong> for dev/test environments
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>4 migration strategies</strong>: DDL, Incremental, Production,
          Multi-Agent
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Zero-downtime deploys</strong>: Blue/green support
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Deterministic execution</strong>: Reproducible results
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Dependency tracking</strong>: Automatic ordering
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Why It Exists</h2>
      <p>
        Traditional migration tools (Alembic, Flyway, Liquibase) are slow and
        not optimized for PostgreSQL:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Per-migration overhead costs 500ms+ each</li>
        <li>No build strategy optimization for test environments</li>
        <li>Manual coordination for parallel migrations</li>
        <li>Limited zero-downtime capabilities</li>
      </ul>
      <p>confiture solves this with PostgreSQL-native optimization strategies.</p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Migration Strategies</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>DDL Build</strong>: Create full schema from scratch (<1s for
          complex schemas)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Incremental</strong>: Apply deltas sequentially (local dev
          friendly)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Production Sync</strong>: Zero-downtime blue/green with
          automated failover
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Multi-Agent</strong>: Parallel execution with coordination
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Performance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Dev/test environments</strong>: 600× faster (1s vs 10min)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Production deploys</strong>: Zero-downtime with 99.99%
          uptime
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Dependency resolution</strong>: O(n) instead of O(n²)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Rollback capability</strong>: Instant rollback with snapshots
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Language</strong>: Rust (high-performance coordination)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Database</strong>: PostgreSQL 13+ (native SQL DDL)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Concurrency</strong>: Tokio for parallel execution
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Integration with Other Tools</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>fraiseql</strong>: Used during compilation to validate schema
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>fraisier</strong>: Deployment orchestrator uses confiture for
          production migrations
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>fraiseql-seed</strong>: Works together for test environment setup
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Quick Start</h2>
      <pre><code># Install
npm install confiture-cli

# Define migrations (YAML)
migrations:
  001-users:
    sql: CREATE TABLE users (id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY)
  002-orders:
    sql: CREATE TABLE orders (id BIGSERIAL, user_id BIGINT REFERENCES users)

# Apply migrations
confiture migrate --strategy=ddl  # Dev/test
confiture migrate --strategy=production-sync  # Production</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>GitHub Repository</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/confiture" target="_blank">
          Visit confiture on GitHub →
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Related Tools</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/ecosystem/fraiseql-core">fraiseql</a> – Core engine</li>
        <li><a href="/ecosystem/fraiseql-seed">fraiseql-seed</a> – Test data</li>
        <li><a href="/ecosystem">← Back to Ecosystem</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <a href="/">← Back to Home</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
